import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins='auto', edgecolor='black')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of ages in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_age = np.mean(data['age'])
    plt.hist(data['age'], bins=20, alpha=0.75)
    plt.axvline(avg_age, color='r', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Average Age: {avg_age:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average age of people in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    plt.axhline(y=avg_height, color='r', linestyle='-', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f} cm')
    
    plt.hist(data['height'], bins=20, alpha=0.75)
    plt.xlabel('Height (cm)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the average height of people in the dataset?')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
